GEO:39.169144;-86.519739
SUMMARY:April First Thursdays at the Eskenazi Museum of Art
DESCRIPTION:Museum Activities for April First Thursdays:4ŌĆō7 p.m. Unwind
  at the Museum    Live music and crafting celebrating featured exhibit Mu
 lyana: Vital Ecosystems. (https://events.iu.edu/artmuseum/event/2123873-d
 rop-in-tours-and-crafting)5 p.m. Artist Talk\,Rania Matar: Where Do I Go?
  ┘ä┘ł┘Ŗ┘å ž▒┘łžŁž¤    Catch this special artist talk with photographer Ra
 nia Matar\, who will share insights into her creative practice and the po
 werful portraits. More info and RSVP here. (https://events.iu.edu/event/2
 104756-artist-talk-rania-matar-where-do-i-go-) (2nd Floor\, Martin Common
 s)  5:45 p.m. Special Performance\, Listening to Coral Bones    Experienc
 e a live performance by dancer and performance artist Utam Moses\, who br
 ings Mulyana's work to life while wearing the artist's sculptural coral-i
 nspired costume Form of Silence. The performance begins in the gallery at
  5:45 p.m. before moving out toward the Arts Plaza and the First Thursday
  festival.  Special Giveaway: Tag the museum in a Mulyana: Vital Ecosyste
 ms exhibition photo on social media for a giveaway item while supplies la
 st! (confirm post at giveaway station\, 1st floor atrium)  Newkirk Gift S
 hop Open (2ndFloor Atrium)Know Before You GoThis event is part of the Fir
 st Thursdays festivals showcase. (https://artsandhumanities.indiana.edu/c
 ouncil-programs/first-thursdays/index.html)Read aboutwhere to find us\, w
 here to park\, accessibility\, and museum guidelines.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><strong>Museum Activities for April First
  Thursdays:</strong></p><div id="lw_cal_event_detail_description" class="
 lw_cal_event_detail_block"><p><strong><span data-contrast="none">4ŌĆō7 p.
 m. Unwind at the Museum</span></strong></p><p>    Live music and crafting
  celebrating featured exhibit <em><a href="https://events.iu.edu/artmuseu
 m/event/2123873-drop-in-tours-and-crafting" target="_blank" rel="noopener
 ">Mulyana: Vital Ecosystems.</a></em></p><p aria-level="2"><strong><span 
 data-contrast="none">5 p.m. Artist Talk\,</span><em>Rania Matar: Where Do
  I Go? ┘ä┘ł┘Ŗ┘å ž▒┘łžŁž¤</em></strong></p><p>    Catch this special artis
 t talk with photographer Rania Matar\, who will share insights into her c
 reative practice and the powerful portraits. <a href="https://events.iu.e
 du/event/2104756-artist-talk-rania-matar-where-do-i-go-" target="_blank" 
 rel="noopener">More info and RSVP here.</a> (2nd Floor\, Martin Commons) 
  </p><p class="x_ms-outlook-mobile-reference-message x_skipProofing"><str
 ong>5:45 p.m. Special Performance\, <em>Listening to Coral Bones</em></st
 rong></p><p class="x_ms-outlook-mobile-reference-message x_skipProofing">
     Experience a live performance by dancer and performance artist Utam M
 oses\, who brings Mulyana's work to life while wearing the artist's sculp
