DESCRIPTION:In honor of the nation's semiquincentennial\, join BesawŌĆöa 
 respected scholar of American art historyŌĆöfor an intimate gallery tour 
 that brings the collection's significance to life. Throughout the visit\,
  she will share her deep passion for the arts and her expertise in the fi
 eld.  About Your Guide  Mindy N. Besaw\, Ph. D\, is the Wilma E. Kelley D
 irector of the IU Eskenazi Museum of Art and a scholar of American Art Hi
 story. As director\, Besaw oversees all facets of the museum's strategy\,
  operations\, and engagement\, including exhibitions\, collections\, teac
 hing partnerships\, and public programming. Read her bio. (https://artmus
 eum.indiana.edu/about/staff/_director/besaw-mindy.html)Know Before You Go
 Space is limited to 15 participants. RSVP to reserve a space. Walk-ins ar
 e welcome if space is available. If this page says "registration has clos
 ed"\, this means that registration and the waitlist have filled.  Plan to
  arrive early to check in. At 1:25 p.m.\, any unclaimed spaces may be rel
 eased to guests who are standing by waiting for a space.  A small handbag
  may be carried at your side. Larger bags and backpacks will need to be s
 tored before touring.  Read about where to find us\, where to park\, acce
 ssibility\, and museum guidelines (https://artmuseum.indiana.edu/visit/yo
 ur-visit.html).  If you park in the IMU parking lot\, Guest Services can 
 validate your parking voucher for a discount.
