DESCRIPTION:On view: April 7ŌĆō18Artist talks: Friday\, April 10\, 4:30 p
 m (Fine Arts 015)Opening reception: Friday\, April 10\, 6ŌĆō8 pm  This ex
 hibition features work created by graduating Master of Fine Arts students
  in the Eskenazi School of Art\, Architecture + Design at Indiana Univers
 ity.  The MFA Thesis Exhibitions represent the culmination of each studen
 t's graduate research in the arts. Students work with the Gallery to plan
  and install their thesis work. The exhibition features graduate student 
 work from a variety of studio areas: ceramics\, digital arts\, fibers\, g
 raphic design\, metalsmithing &amp\; jewelry design\, painting\, photogra
 phy\, printmaking\, and sculpture.MFA Group 2 ArtistsSookyung Augustin: M
 etalsmithing &amp\; Jewelry Design  Shawn Bailey: Digital Art  Jingyin Ch
 e: Photography  Alison Cofrancesco: Painting  McKenzie Phelps: Fibers  Je
 sse Robinson: Ceramics  Matthew Wilhelm: Ceramics  Grunwald Gallery hours
  are TuesdayŌĆōSaturday\, 12ŌĆō4pm\, or by appointment\, and is closed Su
 nday and Monday. All events are free and open to the public and the Grunw
 ald Gallery is accessible to people with disabilities.
