BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:IU Eskenazi School of Art, Architecture + Design
DTSTART:20260414T190000Z
DTEND:20260414T203000Z
LOCATION:SIDNEY AND LOIS ESKENAZI MUSEUM OF ART - Room Number: Roehm Fami
 ly Art-making Studio
GEO:39.169144;-86.519739
SUMMARY:Tattoo Design Workshop
DESCRIPTION:Have you always wanted to design your own tattoos\, but never
  known where to find inspiration? Start at the museum!  This monthly work
 shop provides instructions for examining art to find personal meaning ins
 ide it\, and how to use that meaning to design tattoos based on your own 
 life! Supplies will be provided to design tattoos. Occasional guests from
  the local tattooing community may be featured to answer questions about 
 tattoo design\, tattoo processes\, or the fascinating history of tattoos.
   This group meets on the 2nd Tuesday of every month\, excluding holidays
  and museum closures. The group will meet in the Roehm Family Art-making 
 Studio\, located inside the Simpson Center for Education on the 2nd floor
  of the Eskenazi Museum of Art.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Have you always wanted to design your o
 wn tattoos\, but never known where to find inspiration? Start at the muse
 um!</p><p>  This monthly workshop provides instructions for examining art
  to find personal meaning inside it\, and how to use that meaning to desi
 gn tattoos based on your own life! Supplies will be provided to design ta
 ttoos. Occasional guests from the local tattooing community may be featur
 ed to answer questions about tattoo design\, tattoo processes\, or the fa
 scinating history of tattoos.</p><p>  This group meets on the 2nd Tuesday
  of every month\, excluding holidays and museum closures. The group will 
 meet in the Roehm Family Art-making Studio\, located inside the Simpson C
 enter for Education on the 2nd floor of the Eskenazi Museum of Art.</p>
