SUMMARY:Amy Franceschini | Presence as Practice | Lecture
DESCRIPTION:Working in both urban and rural contexts where intricate soci
 al structures are intertwined with infrastructure and the complexities of
  collective memories embedded in (and around) a site\,Futurefarmerscultiv
 ate public life in place.Amy Franceschini is an artist and founder ofFutu
 refarmers\, a group of international artists\, architects\, computer prog
 rammers\, writers\,farmersand anthropologists whose practices coalesce in
  many formsŌĆöfrom the far-reaching digital realms to the deeply rooted e
 arthly domains.The GuggenheimMuseumshowcasedthe San Francisco-based colle
 ctive in the show "Intervals:Futurefarmers" in 2011. Franceschini has als
 oexhibitedat the Museum of Modern Art(2008)\,the 2000 Whitney Biennial\,t
 he2017Sharjah Biennale\,and the2018Taipei Biennale.Presented by the Desig
 n Speaker Series at the Eskenazi School of Art\, Architecture + Design.
