SUMMARY:Arts\, Humanities\, AI\, and Happiness: How can our lives be cont
 inuously good?
DESCRIPTION:IU arts and humanities faculty are invited to participate in 
 the last of four conversations in this semester's series "Human Questions
  on Arts\, Humanities\, and AI" supported by a grant from the Big Ten Aca
 demic Alliance Arts &amp\; Humanities Leadership Fellows program. The top
 ic of the conversation will be "Arts\, Humanities\, AI\, and Happiness: H
 ow can our lives be continuously good?" and may cover the following inqui
 ries:How do we define human happiness\, flourishing\, and wellbeing? How 
 have these definitions changed?        How do knowledge\, autonomy\, work
 \, and interaction shape human happiness (in a world shaped by AI)?      
     How does AI change society?
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  IU arts and humanities faculty are invi
 ted to participate in the last of four conversations in this semester's s
 eries "Human Questions on Arts\, Humanities\, and AI" supported by a gran
 t from the Big Ten Academic Alliance Arts &amp\; Humanities Leadership Fe
 llows program. The topic of the conversation will be "Arts\, Humanities\,
  AI\, and Happiness: How can our lives be continuously good?" and may cov
 er the following inquiries:</p><ul><li>How do we define human happiness\,
  flourishing\, and wellbeing? How have these definitions changed?  </li><
 li><div role="presentation">      How do knowledge\, autonomy\, work\, an
 d interaction shape human happiness (in a world shaped by AI)?    </div><
 /li><li><div class="x_elementToProof" role="presentation">      How does 
 AI change society?    </div></li></ul>
