SUMMARY:Cross-Pollination Luncheon: A Hoosier Herbarium
DESCRIPTION:Join the Environmental Futures in the Arts and Humanities Ini
 tiative for our final 2025-2026 lunch-hour discussion in a series designe
 d to bring together scholars and artists in the arts and humanities whose
  work engages with plant worldsŌĆöwhether through histories of medicinal 
 plants\, Indigenous knowledges\, botanical writing\, and/or global trade.
  Together we will consider what it means to think and create with plants.
  Each lunch will feature a panel of faculty who will informally share the
 ir work-in-progress.  Our final Cross-Pollination lunch will focus on an 
 interdisciplinary\, multi-media project inspired by the IU Herbarium.  Pa
 nelists for the April 17 lunch will be...Shannon Gayk  Rich Hull  Roger H
 angarter  Jennifer Lau    Lunch will be provided to all registered attend
 ees. Please RSVP below.
