SUMMARY:Futurhythm Machines
DESCRIPTION:Beginning with a hands-on synthesizer session led by the Cent
 er for Concrete and Abstract Machines (CCAM (https://nam12.safelinks.prot
 ection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fccam.world%2F&amp\;data=05%7C02%7Ce
 czarse%40iu.edu%7Ca7d139f738e044bfc7d208de8b700e54%7C1113be34aed14d00ab4b
 cdd02510be91%7C1%7C0%7C639101511060812708%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB
 0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldU
 IjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp\;sdata=zKxu9WOigZcAhF1yNjeZwS9g9ig36cUddl7r
 5MEQMwg%3D&amp\;reserved=0)) in Chicago\, the event opens into an informa
 l\, drop-in experience where visitors are welcome to observe\, listen\, a
 nd engage at their own pace.  Watch as artists experiment with custom-bui
 lt analog instruments\, generating evolving soundscapes through collectiv
 e listening and physical interaction. The event concludes with an informa
 l jam session featuring audio-responsive visuals and closing conversation
  that situates the activity within the cultural lineage of Chicago House 
 music and related experimental traditions. Together\, these practices hig
 hlight alternative approaches to creative technology while helping us ima
 gine the technology-rich futures we aspire to build.Guests may come and g
 o throughout.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p class="elementToProof">  Beginning with a
  hands-on synthesizer session led by the Center for Concrete and Abstract
  Machines (<a id="OWA30eb7d45-5069-fdd9-5c23-6f84884055e6" class="OWAAuto
 Link" title="Original URL: https://ccam.world/ Click to follow link." hre
 f="https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fccam
 .world%2F&amp\;data=05%7C02%7Ceczarse%40iu.edu%7Ca7d139f738e044bfc7d208de
 8b700e54%7C1113be34aed14d00ab4bcdd02510be91%7C1%7C0%7C639101511060812708%
 7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiO
 iJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp\;sdata=zKxu9
 WOigZcAhF1yNjeZwS9g9ig36cUddl7r5MEQMwg%3D&amp\;reserved=0" target="_blank
 " rel="noopener noreferrer" data-auth="NotApplicable" data-outlook-id="04
 b548bd-aff6-44a9-be78-234a2d5f1714" data-linkindex="1">CCAM</a>) in Chica
 go\, the event opens into an informal\, drop-in experience where visitors
  are welcome to observe\, listen\, and engage at their own pace.</p><p cl
 ass="elementToProof">  Watch as artists experiment with custom-built anal
 og instruments\, generating evolving soundscapes through collective liste
 ning and physical interaction. The event concludes with an informal jam s
 ession featuring audio-responsive visuals and closing conversation that s
 ituates the activity within the cultural lineage of Chicago House music a
 nd related experimental traditions. Together\, these practices highlight 
 alternative approaches to creative technology while helping us imagine th
 e technology-rich futures we aspire to build.</p><p class="elementToProof
 "><strong>Guests may come and go throughout.</strong></p>
