 gn at Indiana University.The B.F.A. Thesis Exhibition represents the culm
 ination of each student's research in the arts. Students work with the ga
 llery to plan and install their thesis work.The exhibition features gradu
 ate student work from a variety of studio areas: digital arts\, graphic d
 esign\, metalsmithing &amp\; jewelry design\, painting\, photography\, an
 d printmaking.Opening reception: Friday\, April 24\, 6ŌĆō8pmExhibiting ar
 tists:Hannah Dinius: Graphic DesignLane Egyhazi: Metals &amp\; Jewelry De
