DESCRIPTION:May 1\, 2026\, 9:30 AM - 12:30 PMFerguson International Cente
 r\, 4th FloorPoster Set-up: 8:45ŌĆō9:20 AM  Light Breakfast: 9:00ŌĆō9:30 
 AM  Keynote Address by Judd Devermont: 9:30ŌĆō10:45 AM  Poster Session: 1
 1:00 AM ŌĆō 12:30 PM  Discover Global Learning at IU Bloomington!  Join u
 s for the IU Global Learning Showcase\, a celebration of student and facu
 lty innovation in globally engaged education.  This year's keynote addres
 s\, "Reimagining Strategies Toward Sub-Saharan Africa: Opportunities for 
 U.S. Cities\, Communities\, and Universities\," will be delivered by Judd
  Devermont\, former National Security Council Senior Director for African
  Affairs and National Intelligence Officer for Africa. He will share less
 ons learned from drafting the Biden Administration's strategy toward the 
 region and discuss opportunities for Indiana's institutions\, leaders\, a
 nd citizens to model a new\, more mutually advantageous partnership.  Aft
 er the keynote\, explore a poster sessionfeaturing presentations from glo
 bal client projects\, Collaborative Online International Learning (COIL)\
 , Diplomacy Lab\, and more. Topics span disciplines and highlight how IU 
 students and faculty are turning learning into action on some of today's 
 most pressing global challenges.All are welcomeŌĆöcome be inspired and jo
 in us in shaping a more connected world!  Present Your Work at the Poster
  SessionAre you a student or instructor engaged in global learning on an 
 IU campus? We invite you to share your work during the poster session! Th
 is is a great opportunity to showcase experiential learning projects\, co
 nnect with others\, and highlight how global learning is happening right 
 here in Indiana. Poster printing costs will be covered.&#160\;  Please fi
 ll out this brief interest form (https://iuglobal-fireform.eas.iu.edu/onl
 ine/form/index/cgcgl002) if you would like to participate in the poster s
 ession.  Questions?&#160\; Email global@iu.edu (mailto:global@iu.edu) wit
 h Global Learning Showcase in the subject line.Supported by: IU Global\, 
 the Center for the Study of Global Change
